欧洲疾控中心：欧盟国家正为疫情“全球大流行”做准备。
CDC: European Union countries are preparing for a global pandemic.
王磬。
Chime with Wang.
界面新闻                      。
Interface news.
界面新闻。
Interface news.
界面新闻是中国具有影响力的原创财经新媒体，只服务于独立思考的人群。
Interface News is an original and influential new financial media in China, serving only the people who think independently.
图片来源：IC Photo记者：王磬“ 尽管“全球大流行”听上去比“流行病”更严重，但这种严重加剧主要是指传播规模（scale），而不是该疾病本身的激烈程度（severity）”过去几天，意大利突然激增的新冠肺炎确诊人数，把欧洲推上了风口浪尖。
Photo: IC Photo: "Although the" global pandemic "sounds more serious than" epidemic, "the severe increase mainly refers to the scale of transmission rather than the intensity of the disease itself." In the past few days, the number of confirmed cases of new crown pneumonia in Italy has pushed Europe to the fore.
2月24日，欧洲疾控中心（European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control）同世界卫生组织一道向意大利派出了专家组。
On February 24, the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, together with the World Health Organization, sent a team of experts to Italy.
欧洲疾控中心是欧盟下属的独立机构，其职责是加强欧洲对传染病的防御能力。
The European Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) is an independent agency of the European Union whose role is to strengthen Europe's defense against infectious diseases.
2003年非典爆发之后，欧洲国家形成共识，需要有一个跨欧洲的传染病防治协调组织。
In the wake of the SARS outbreak in 2003, European countries agreed on the need for a trans-European coordination organization for infectious diseases.
欧洲疾控中心于2004年在瑞典应运而生。
The European CDC emerged in Sweden in 2004.
在应对禽流感、中东呼吸症等全球疫情时，欧洲疾控中心曾发挥了不少作用。
The CDC has been instrumental in responding to global outbreaks such as avian flu and respiratory disease in the Middle East.
界面新闻就意大利疫情、欧洲对策、全球走势等话题邮件专访了欧洲疾控中心。
Interface News interviewed CDC in Europe on topics such as Italian epidemic, European countermeasures, global trends, etc.
欧洲疾控中心表示，疫情正在极具动态地发展，预计接下来几天中会有更多的确诊病例。
The CDC says the epidemic is developing very dynamically, with more confirmed cases expected in the next few days.
如果观察到病毒在欧洲的持续传播，将需要激活目前已经存在于欧盟各国的大流行病防范计划。
If continued transmission of the virus is observed in Europe, it will be necessary to activate pandemic preparedness plans that already exist in EU countries.
这是一个全球性的问题，协调是关键。
This is a global issue, and coordination is key.
以下是专访全文：界面新闻：鉴于上周在韩国、伊朗和意大利发生的疫情，COVID-19疫情是否正在进入“全球大流行”（pandemic）的阶段？欧洲疾控中心：将某一种疫情宣布为“全球大流行”，这是世卫组织的职责。
Given last week's outbreaks in South Korea, Iran, and Italy, is COVID-19 entering the stage of a "global pandemic"? The European CDC: It is the responsibility of WHO to declare an epidemic as a "global pandemic."
“疫情爆发”（outbreak）是指，给定的时间段内，一种疾病在特定地点和人群中发生的比例比通常预期的要多。
Outbreak means that, over a given period of time, a disease occurs in a larger proportion of a given place and population than would normally be expected.
“流行病”（epidemic）跟“疫情爆发”本质上是同一件事，但往往意味着更严重的情况。
An "epidemic" is essentially the same thing as an "outbreak," but it often means a more serious situation.
“疫情爆发”在某种程度上暗示着它的地理局限性，但“流行病”则推示了可能扩散的危机局势。
The "outbreak" implies, in part, its geographical limitations, but the "epidemic" suggests potentially proliferating crisis situations.
二者的差别很细微，但也很重要。
The difference between the two is subtle but also important.
相比之下，“全球大流行”（pandemic）是指“流行病”进入全球广泛传播的阶段，通常会影响数量巨大的人群。
A "global pandemic," by contrast, is a phase in which an "epidemic" enters a global epidemic, usually affecting a large number of people.
值得注意的是，尽管“全球大流行”听上去比“流行病”更严重，但这种严重加剧主要是指传播规模（scale），而不是该疾病本身的激烈程度（severity）。
It is worth noting that, while the "global pandemic" sounds more serious than an "epidemic," the severity of the increase refers more to the scale of transmission (scale) than to the severity of the disease itself.
界面新闻：意大利到目前为止还在寻找“零号病人”，这也意味着暂时无法还原传染链条。
Interface News: Italy has so far been looking for "patient number zero," which means it is temporarily impossible to restore the transmission chain.
它的难点主要在哪里？欧洲疾控中心：这并不是当下最值得关心的问题。
What are the main difficulties? CDC: This is not the biggest concern right now.
现阶段，减少感染传播的最佳方法是快速识别和测试疑似病例，以及识别和监视他们的近距离接触者。
At this stage, the best way to reduce the spread of infection is to quickly identify and test suspected cases, as well as to identify and monitor their close contacts.
意大利当前的情况表明本地传播可能导致了多个聚集性传染事件。
The current situation in Italy suggests that local transmission can lead to multiple episodes of concentrated sexually transmitted infections.
并非所有报告的病例都具有明确的流行病学链条，例如中国旅行史或是与确诊病人的接触。
Not all reported cases have a clear epidemiological chain, such as a Chinese travel history or contact with a confirmed patient.
情况正在极具动态性地发展，我们预计接下来几天中会有更多的确诊病例。
The situation is developing very dynamically, and we expect more cases to be confirmed in the next few days.
界面新闻：欧盟各成员国之间没有边境管控，这是否意味着疫情将会很快席卷欧洲？欧洲疾控中心：在当前的阶段，欧洲可能会出现额外的输入性病例。
Interface News: Without border controls among EU member states, does this mean that the epidemic will soon engulf Europe? CDC: At this stage, Europe may have additional cases of imported cases.
为了减轻疫情在欧盟/欧洲经济区内部传播的风险，成员国们正在调整它们关于大流行病的防范计划（pandemic preparedness plans），以更好地应对这场疫情。
To mitigate the risk of the epidemic spreading within the EU / EEA, member states are adjusting their pandemic preparedness plans to better respond to the epidemic.
如果我们观察到了病毒在欧洲的持续传播，我们将需要激活这些已经存在于欧盟各国的大流行病防范计划。
If we observe the continued spread of the virus in Europe, we will need to activate these pandemic preparedness plans that already exist in EU countries.
这可能意味着需要专注于非药物性的防疫措施（non-pharmaceutical countermeasures），例如，保证医疗系统拥有足够的资源和人力去隔离和治疗不断增长的新冠病人。
This may imply a need to focus on non-pharmacological prophylaxis, for example, by ensuring that the health-care system has sufficient resources and manpower to isolate and treat the growing number of patients in the new crown.
我们需要跟公众继续保持非常明晰的风险沟通，以让公众了解事实、理解并遵守公共卫生检疫。
We need to maintain very clear risk communication with the public in order to understand the facts, understand and comply with public health quarantine.
这是一个全球性的问题，协调是关键。
This is a global issue, and coordination is key.
界面新闻：欧洲现在有多少实验室能够进行诊断测试？欧洲疾控中心：有如下实验室可以进行诊断测试，包括初步诊断或是确认诊断。
Interface News: How many laboratories in Europe are now able to perform diagnostic tests? CDC: The following laboratories are available for diagnostic testing, including initial diagnosis or confirmation of diagnosis.
可以将任何阳性测试的结果发送到这些实验室进行确认：德国：罗伯特·科赫研究所–柏林大学病毒学研究所（德国冠状病毒诊断工作组，Charité病毒学研究所，冠状病毒国家顾问实验室，世界卫生组织新兴感染和生物威胁合作中心）德国：马尔堡理工学院荷兰：鹿特丹伊拉斯莫斯医学中心病毒科学系荷兰：国家公共卫生与环境研究所（RIVM）英国：英国公共卫生部呼吸道病毒科法国：巴黎巴斯德研究所斯洛文尼亚：卢布尔雅那大学微生物学和免疫学研究所瑞典：瑞典公共卫生署界面新闻：如果确诊人数从目前的一两百人增长到几千人、甚至更多，欧洲是否有足够的医院或护理人员来应对疫情？欧洲疾控中心：在流感季节的高峰期，欧盟/欧洲经济区和英国的医疗保健系统的风险通常维持在低至中度。
The results of any positive tests can be sent to these laboratories for validation: Germany: Robert Koch Institute - Virology Institute of the University of Berlin (Working Group on Coronavirus Diagnostics of Germany, Charité Virology Institute, Coronavirus National Consulting Laboratory, WHO ESRM).
界面新闻：欧盟层面可以采取怎样的措施来应对疫情？欧洲疾控中心：在当前阶段，减少感染传播的最佳方法是快速识别和测试疑似病例，以及识别和监视密切接触者。
Interface News: What can be done at the EU level to deal with the epidemic? CDC: At this stage, the best way to reduce the spread of infection is to quickly identify and test suspected cases, as well as to identify and monitor close contacts.
应当向公众科普能够降低传染风险的行为，例如手部和呼吸道的卫生；一旦出现症状或是与高危人群接触，应当在家自我隔离并寻求医学建议。
Behaviour that reduces the risk of infection, such as hand and respiratory hygiene, should be made available to the public; self-segregation and medical advice should be sought at home in the event of symptoms or contact with high-risk groups.
在过去的经验中，例如防治非典和中东呼吸综合征（MERS）时，这些系统性的防治措施被认为是有效的。
In past experiences, such as SARS and the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS), these systemic responses were considered effective.
